ANGULAR INSTALLATION STEPS--->
  1) Install node.js from https://nodejs.org/en/download/current/
	2) node -v to check node.js version
	3) npm install -g @angular/cli  to install angular cli on windows
	4) ng --version to check angular version
	5) ng new my-dream-app
	6) Cd my-dream-app
	7) Hit command ng serve to run the application.
	8) Hit localhost:4200

CREATE COMPONENTS IN ANGULAR--->
  ng g c product-add --skipTests=true
	ng g c product-get --skipTests=true
	ng g c product-edit --skipTests=true


Configure Angular Routing Progress Indicator:
It's third party package.
	npm install ng2-slim-loading-bar --save

If we want to bridge the gap between Angular 8 and the third-party packages
	npm install rxjs-compat --save

https://jasonwatmore.com/post/2019/06/10/angular-8-user-registration-and-login-example-tutorial
